revision.text:
[[Image:Map of Brezovica District (Zagreb).svg|thumb|right|Brezovica as a part of [[Zagreb]]]] [[Image:Dvorac Brezovica južni ulaz.jpg|thumb|right|[[Brezovica castle]] view]] '''Brezovica''' ({{IPA-sh|brêzoʋit͡sa|hr}}) is a city district of [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]]. It is located in the southwestern part of the city and has 12,030 inhabitants (as of 2011).<ref>{{Croatian Census 2011|url=http://www.dzs.hr/Eng/censuses/census2011/results/htm/e01_01_01_cet/E01_01_01_zup21_cet.html|title=Population by Age and Sex, by Districts of City of Zagreb, 2011 Census}}</ref> It is one of the more rural districts in Zagreb. The [[A1 (Croatia)|A1]] highway passes through Brezovica, although it has no exits there.
Of note is [[Dvorac Brezovica]], an eighteenth-century chateau now owned by the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Zagreb|Zagreb Archdiocese]]. Dvorac Brezovica (castle) has been abandoned for several years and the building and its surroundings have fallen into disrepair.
