Below is a list of those who have held the office of '''Governor of the [[Isle of Wight]]''' in England. Lord Mottistone was the last Lord Lieutenant to hold the title Governor, from 1992 to 1995, since then there has been no Governor appointed.
==Governors of the Isle of Wight==
*1509–1520: Sir [[Nicholas Wadham (d. 1542)|Nicholas I Wadham]] (d.1542) "Captain of the Isle of Wight".<ref>[http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1509-1558/member/wadham-sir-nicholas-1472-1542 Virgoe, Roger, Biography of Wadham, Sir Nicholas (by 1472-1542), of Merrifield, nr. Ilton, Som., Published in The History of Parliament: House of Commons 1509-1558, ed. S.T. Bindoff, 1982]</ref> *1520–1538: Sir James Worsley <ref>http://www.iwhistory.org.uk/RM/minorforts/</ref> *1538&ndash;1540: [[Thomas Cromwell, 1st Earl of Essex|Thomas Cromwell, 1st Baron Cromwell]] (later Earl of Essex) *1540–1553: [[Richard Worsley (16th century MP)|Richard Worsley]] <ref name= HoP> {{cite web| url=http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1509-1558/member/worsley-richard-1517-65|title= WORSLEY, Richard (by 1517-65), of Appuldurcombe in Godshill, I.o.W.|publisher= History of Parliament Online|accessdate= 1 October 2016}} </ref> *1553–1558: Sir William Girling *1558–1560: The Hon. John Paulet, Lord St John, later Earl of Wiltshire, and finally, [[John Paulet, 2nd Marquess of Winchester]] *1560–1565: [[Richard Worsley (16th century MP)|Richard Worsley]] (reappointed)<ref name= HoP/> *1565–1583: [[Edward Horsey|Sir Edward Horsey]] *1583–1603: [[George Carey, 2nd Baron Hunsdon|Sir George Carey, 2nd Lord Hunsdon]] *1603–1624: [[Henry Wriothesley, 3rd Earl of Southampton]] *1633–1642: [[Jerome Weston, 2nd Earl of Portland]] *1642–1647: [[Philip Herbert, 4th Earl of Pembroke]] *1647–1647: [[Robert Hammond (English army officer)|Robert Hammond]] *1648–1659: Col. [[William Sydenham]] *1660: [[Anthony Ashley Cooper, 1st Earl of Shaftesbury]] *1660–1661: [[Jerome Weston, 2nd Earl of Portland]] *1661–1667: [[Thomas Colepeper, 2nd Baron Colepeper]] *1668–1692: [[Robert Holmes (admiral)|Sir Robert Holmes]] *1693: [[Thomas Tollemache|Hon. Thomas Tollemache]] *1693–1707: [[John Cutts, 1st Baron Cutts]] *1707–1710: [[Charles Paulet, 2nd Duke of Bolton]] *1710–1715: [[John Richmond Webb|General John Richmond Webb]] *1715–1726: [[William Cadogan, 1st Earl Cadogan|William Cadogan]] (later Earl Cadogan)<ref>{{London Gazette | issue=5360 |page=3 | date=30 August 1715}}</ref> *1726–1733: [[Charles Paulet, 3rd Duke of Bolton]] *1733–1734: [[John Montagu, 2nd Duke of Montagu]] *1734–1742: [[John Wallop, 1st Earl of Portsmouth|John Wallop, 1st Viscount Lymington]] *1742–1746: [[Charles Paulet, 3rd Duke of Bolton]] *1746–1762: [[John Wallop, 1st Earl of Portsmouth]] *1763–1764: [[Thomas Holmes, 1st Baron Holmes]] *1764–1766: [[Hans Stanley]] *1766–1770: [[Harry Paulet, 6th Duke of Bolton]] *1770–1780: [[Hans Stanley]] *1780–1782: [[Sir Richard Worsley, 7th Baronet]] *1782–1791: [[Harry Paulet, 6th Duke of Bolton]] <!-- or 1782–1789? --> *1791–1807: [[Thomas Orde-Powlett, 1st Baron Bolton]] <!-- or 1789–1807? --> *1807–1841: [[James Harris, 2nd Earl of Malmesbury]] *1841–1857: [[William à Court, 1st Baron Heytesbury]] *1857–1888: [[Charles Shaw-Lefevre, 1st Viscount Eversley]] *1889–1896: [[Prince Henry of Battenberg]] *1896–1944: [[Princess Beatrice of the United Kingdom]] *1957–1965: [[Gerald Wellesley, 7th Duke of Wellington]] *1965–1974: [[Louis Mountbatten, 1st Earl Mountbatten of Burma]] (Lord Lieutenant 1974–1979) *1992–1995: [[David Seely, 4th Baron Mottistone]]
