{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Newell Falls | photo = | photo_width = 250px | photo_caption = | map = New South Wales | relief = yes | map_width = 250px | coordinates = {{coord|30|23|55|S|152|45|35|E|type:waterbody_region:AU-NSW_scale:50000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref name=GNR>{{NSW GNR|id=ujqwvqUlMn|title=Newell Falls|accessdate=15 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Gazetteer of Australia|id=NSW42178|name=Newell Falls (NSW)}}</ref> | location = [[New England (New South Wales)|New England]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]] | type = | elevation = | height = | height_longest = | number_drops = | width = | average_width = | watercourse = ''unnamed stream'' | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Newell Falls''' is a [[waterfall]] on an unnamed stream that is located in the [[New England (New South Wales)|New England]] region of [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]].
==Location and features== The waterfall is situated adjacent to the [[Waterfall Way]] between the town of {{NSWcity|Dorrigo}} and the locality of {{NSWcity|Thora}} in [[Dorrigo National Park]]. The waterfall passes down the cliff side and under a single lane bridge before entering the [[Bellinger River]] at the bottom of the valley. People can also stop to view the waterfall at small rest area, around {{convert|50|m}} from the Newell Falls. Picnic tables, shelter sheds and bins are located at this site. There is also a near Newell Falls lookout into the Bellinger Valley.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-of-waterfalls.com/australia-newell-falls.html|title=Newell Falls and Sherrard Falls|work=World of Waterfalls|date=7 May 2008|accessdate=15 May 2014}}</ref>
The Waterfall Way often closes at Newell Falls in times of heavy rainfall and flooding as the road becomes a shower of water and visibility is significantly reduced.
